The paper discusses indexing schemes for similarity-based search, which is a common problem in information retrieval (cs.IR), databases (cs.DB), and machine learning (cs.LG, cs.CV). The paper also discusses the high-dimensional geometry of similarity workloads, which is relevant to algorithms and data structures (cs.DS) used in these fields.
